<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> When I saw this had happened this morning I immediately, after uttering lots of curse words and wiping the foam from the sides of my mouth, started to question the timing of this change.<br>
<br>
They had to patch in the little gnome and all of this as a ninja patch...and why do it now?<br>
<br>
I started doing some digging and this is what I uncovered. The sources on this are all 3rd-4th hand at best as no one seems to want to take credit for causing this massive nerf....but it has the ring of truth to it so I figured I would share.<br>
<br>
Anyone who has been in EarthB knows that you can happily reside in the zone if you are flagged for Elemental access. In fact you only needed the key for the actual act of ferrying people in...once zoned over you were welcome to stay as long as you liked assuming you could already zone into EarthA.<br>
<br>
After details of the Rathe encounter became public a guild on one of the more crowded servers got a devilish idea in their minds and decided to let in ALL THE OTHER GUILDS on the same server who were elementally capable to make one massive zerg run on the Rathe. If the problem was the summoning munchkins and having enough DPS and Hps to kill them all fast...well why not quadruple or quintuple the force?<br>
<br>
So 200+ people zone into EarthB and spread out as best they can in 4 seperate raid groups...mow their way to the Council area and engage the munchkins with an amazingly effective zerg force....albeit unsuccessfully. Even though the zerg force failed Sony quickly realizes that a second or third attempt by a better organized Zerg force might actually kill the Rathe...and so they panic and implement the individual key quest with a ninja patch.<br>
<br>
<br>
I'll admit I had a similar idea when someone posted on another thread that it was a perfectly winnable encounter if you had 2 whole raids to do it....I'm not even sure such a thing would work unless only ONE of the raids actually got kill credit on each munchkin....but it might be enough of a possible risk that people might be Time ready before the zone is complete that Sony chose to act sooner rather than later. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
